This article discusses President Obama's plan to ensure that hard work leads to a decent living for every American. The plan includes raising the minimum wage to $9.00, providing high-quality preschool for every child, partnering with communities to help them rebuild and put people back to work, creating pathways to jobs for all Americans, expanding early childhood opportunity for all Americans, and strengthening families. The article also highlights the President's commitment to rewarding hard work, providing access to high-quality education, revitalizing neighborhoods, supporting distressed cities, and providing jobs and skills training for low-income youth and adults.